Description: SimpleMating is a two core package for cross optimization. First, it estimates the performance for a set of crosses, such as mid-parental value, cross total genetic value, and/or usefulness (using additive and/or non-additive effects), allowing for multi-trait scenarios. Furthermore, it uses a mate allocation algorithm to create a mating plan that aims to maximize a target criterion (mid-parental value, cross total genetic value, or usefulness) while constraining the next generation's inbreeding levels.
